Author::::westcorkthinktank
DateTime::::2016-03-08T19:10:44Z
I was fortunate enough to be at the ODI World Cup match at Eden Park between New Zealand and Australia. At half time in what was a pretty high intensity match Martin was inducted the NZ Hall of Fame (or some such thing I think). Knowing of his illness the presenters had a lump in their throat, the Aussies in the crowd, as well as the Kiwi's, had a lump in their throat and you could hear a pin drop when he spoke and the applause at the end seemed as great as when McCullum took on Johnson and whacked him for a couple of sixes. Not a quiver or tremble was there in his voice as he spoke of the pride he had in the way in which the Kiwis were playing their cricket. I don't know how many of us could have managed such single minded concentration that in such circumstances, but maybe that was Martin. I imagine most of us though would be as happy as he was to see the things which we have believed in for most of our lives coming true as we approach death. Perhaps that gave him some of that calmness. 



