Bang on the money as always Andy. As a 46 yr old I enjoyed watching Martin Crowe batting in England many summers ago. The deaths this year of several of our formative icons now makes us acutely aware of our own mortality.It was an emotional rollercoaster reading several of the articles you mention, a mixture of tears at the sadness of his early passing, pride that cricketers and cricket writers can write such emotional and articulate thought,s and a different sort of pride, namely that the qualities of human decentness can be valued and praised. I would love to have my friends say just 10% of the nice things said about MC in these lovely obituaries. It would mean I made a small mark on peoples' lives.Anyway as I said above, a nice round-up Andy and keep up the good work.



